format: This data frame contains the following columns:

parameters.class: a factor, coded to identify the class
parameters.like:
a summary score
based on two of the questions, on a scale from 1 (dislike)
to 12 (like)
parameters.Class: a factor with levels corresponding to each class
parameters.State:
a factor with levels
ACT Australian Capital Territory,
NSW New South Wales
parameters.sex:
a factor with levels
f, m
parameters.school: a factor, coded to identify the school

reference:
Francine Adams,  Rosemary Martin and Murali Nayadu, Australian
National University
description:
Description
The science data frame has 1385 rows and 7 columns.
The data are on attitudes to science, from a survey where there were
results from 20 classes in private schools and 46 classes in public
schools.
title: School Science Survey Data
